 691:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****   * @brief Receive an amount of data in blocking mode till either the expected number of data
 692:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****   *        is received or an IDLE event occurs.
 693:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****   * @note  HAL_OK is returned if reception is completed (expected number of data has been received)
 694:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****   *        or if reception is stopped after IDLE event (less than the expected number of data has b
 695:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****   *        In this case, RxLen output parameter indicates number of data available in reception buf
 696:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****   * @note  When UART parity is not enabled (PCE = 0), and Word Length is configured to 9 bits (M1-M
 697:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****   *        the received data is handled as a set of uint16_t. In this case, Size must indicate the 
 698:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****   *        of uint16_t available through pData.
 699:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****   * @note When FIFO mode is enabled, the RXFNE flag is set as long as the RXFIFO
 700:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****   *       is not empty. Read operations from the RDR register are performed when
 701:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****   *       RXFNE flag is set. From hardware perspective, RXFNE flag and
 702:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****   *       RXNE are mapped on the same bit-field.
 703:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****   * @param huart   UART handle.
 704:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****   * @param pData   Pointer to data buffer (uint8_t or uint16_t data elements).
 705:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****   * @param Size    Amount of data elements (uint8_t or uint16_t) to be received.
 706:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****   * @param RxLen   Number of data elements finally received
 707:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****   *                (could be lower than Size, in case reception ends on IDLE event)
 708:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****   * @param Timeout Timeout duration expressed in ms (covers the whole reception sequence).
